owner.profileText: Hello fellow geocachers I am the Pool guy I love looking for all hides. I will admit some are better than others.

text: With lots of help from the CO I was able to solve this hide ---Thanks Stan for all your hard work in making this puzzle hear is your favorite point.

So a couple years ago on Memorial Day, I went caching with my buddy ocie_mitchell and one of his kids.  We talked about this puzzle, and we determined what we needed to do.  But I had to leave before we got the solution, and then Ocie went and solved it on his own! So I was stuck until about a week ago, and then I realized that I could solve it on my own after all.  It wasn't so much learning something new as remembering something old.  I'm filling my puzzle calendar, and I needed one for today, so I headed over to make the find.  No problems making the find.  This is a fantastic puzzle, and I'm glad to give it a favorite point.  12 more puzzle days to go.  TFTP and C!

This code was mentioned in our GC group as an example for any other gc.
Out of curiosity I googled the code and had to notice it wasn't far away from L.A.

When we came from Las Vegas I used the situation to take this little detour.
The puzzle was great and I've seen it in a riddle before so I knew what I had to ask.
With the help of DJAbreption I could learn some new stuff and how to solve this one.
It is just one simple word you have to know.... I hadn't before.

Thank you for this mystery and the funny code aswell.

Wel leuk een cache in Californie te vinden zonder er heer te gaan.
Dit nummer hadden we als fictief bedacht om een cache in GSAK te zetten.
Misschien komen we er nog wel eens echt, in 2001 zijn we er vlak langs geweest, maar toe lag de cache er nog niet!!
Wie weet, misschien nog eens.
Nice to find a cache in California without going gentleman.
This number had conceived as a fictional to put a cache in GSAK.
Maybe we will get there sometimes really, we are close visited in 2001, but far, yet the cache was !!
Who knows, maybe another
